# Nmap Network Scan Lab

## Overview
This project demonstrates how I used Nmap in a controlled lab environment to identify live hosts, discover open ports, and enumerate running services. The purpose of this lab was to practice reconnaissance and improve my ability to document technical findings like a cybersecurity analyst.

---

## Objective
- Identify live systems in a lab environment
- Discover open ports on the target machine
- Detect running services and versions
- Document findings and possible risks

---

## Tools Used
- Kali Linux
- Nmap

---

## Lab Environment
This lab was performed in a safe and authorized practice environment for learning purposes only.

---

